@kleinsch re-thinking a bit not sure if we need this Factory construct given that this is single class will only be created once in when the spout initializes. Why not try the following
1. add configure method to FailedMsgRetryManager
public interface FailedMsgRetryManager {
     public void configure(Map<String,Object> config)  or public void configure(SpoutConfig config);
}
1. accept fully qualified class name as pluggable instance ( example look for authorizer config in storm-core)
2. by default create instance of ExponentialBackoffMsgRetryManager  . You can use https://github.com/apache/storm/blob/master/storm-core/src/jvm/backtype/storm/utils/Utils.java#L96
3. call configure method with spoutconfig so that it gets all the available options
